1.4 We may change these General Terms at any time. You should check this page regularly for any changes. Any changes will apply from the date that they are uploaded.
1.5 By entering a Promotion you agree that you will be legally bound by these General Terms and any applicable Specific Terms.
2. IDENTITY OF THE PROMOTER OF THE COMPETITION
2.1 The promoter of a competition or prize draw is the person who is responsible for running it. Unless any Specific Terms tell you otherwise, the promoter of the Promotion will be Twinkl Ltd, a company registered in England and Wales under number 07201458 whose registered office is at Wards Exchange, 197 Ecclesall Road, Sheffield, England, S11 8HW (‘we’, ‘our’, ‘us’). You should contact us in the first place if you have any issues or problems in relation to a Promotion. You can write to us at our registered office address or by email at legal@twinkl[dot]co[dot]uk if you have any concern relating to any Promotion, setting out clearly which Promotion and your issue.
2.2 In addition, certain Promotions may provide entrants with additional methods of contacting us, for example posting on a Facebook group or tweeting on a Twitter feed. In these cases, you may also use this method to contact us.
3. COMPETITION ELIGIBILITY RULES
3.1 Unless stated otherwise in the applicable Specific Terms, entrants to our Promotions must be aged 18 or over and must be resident in the UK.
3.2 You may not enter a Promotion if you are:
a) our employee or an employee of our holding or subsidiary companies;
b) an employee of one of our content partners, agents or suppliers who are professionally connected with the Promotion or its administration; or
c) a member of the immediate family or household of a) or b) above.
3.3 Certain Promotions may have additional eligibility requirements, such as a current subscription to our services or a requirement to be engaged in a specified profession. Any such additional eligibility requirements will be stated in the applicable Specific Terms.
3.4 Where a Promotion is open to children (aged 15 or younger) and/or young persons (aged 16 or 17), the age requirements will be stated in the applicable Specific Terms. We may require that the parent or guardian of any person aged under 18 confirms in writing that he/she agrees to be bound by all terms and conditions applicable to the relevant Promotion and will accept any prize on behalf of a prize winner who is under 18.
3.5 We will decide, in our sole discretion, whether any eligibility requirement has or has not been met and we may require evidence or confirmation from entrants at any time before awarding prizes.
4. ENTRY AND ENTRY METHODS
4.1 By online form: Where entry is by filling in and submitting an online form, you will need a device capable of accessing the internet and the form for the applicable Promotion. Online form entries are deemed to be received upon submission confirmation. Entries submitted in this way must be completed with all required details in full as specified in the Specific Terms or indicated with an asterisk (“*”) next to the fillable field of the form. Entries which fail to provide the required details will be void.
4.2 By social media: Where entry is via social media, you will need a device capable of accessing the internet and, depending on the platform on which the Promotion is run, an account for the applicable social media service.
Unless otherwise stated in the Specific Terms, for:
a) a competition requiring a social media post to be posted for entry, the entry will be deemed to be received when and only if the social media post is visible to the public or all members of the group in which it is posted; or
b) a competition requiring a message to be sent to us via social media, the entry will be deemed to be received when the message is received by us.
4.3 By post: Where you enter by post, you must place your entry postcard containing your email address, phone number, name, and any other details specified in the Specific Terms inside an envelope. You may post the entry by any second or first class method of postage. Postal entries must arrive at least one week before the draw date specified in the Specific Terms. Entries not received inside an envelope, later than one week before the draw date, or which are incomplete will not be counted. We will not return any postal entries.
4.4 Deficient Entries: In all Promotions, we reserve the right to reject any entries that are inaudible, incomplete, incomprehensible, damaged or otherwise deficient. We also reserve the right to reject entries that are unlawful, indecent, racist, inflammatory, defamatory or which we consider to be otherwise harmful to the goodwill and reputation of us or our brands. We accept no responsibility for any late, lost or misdirected entries, including but not limited to posts, messages, emails, or online form submissions not received due to technical disruptions, network congestion, spoilage, or any other reason.
4.5 Automated Entry: The use of any automated entry software or any other mechanical or electronic means (in any case otherwise than administered by us as part of the Promotion) that permits any person to enter any Promotion repeatedly is prohibited.
4.6 Names: Entrants must enter Promotions using their legal names. We reserve the right to disqualify any entrant who uses multiple names and to require them to return any prize they may have won.
4.7 Multiple Entries: Unless otherwise permitted pursuant to any Specific Terms, no person may enter a particular Promotion more than once and persons may not enter a Promotion as part of a syndicate or on behalf of any other person, syndicate, group, society or company.
5. PRIZES
5.1 The prize for each Promotion will be as stated in the Specific Terms. We reserve in all cases the right to replace the stated prize with a prize that we consider to be of broadly equivalent value. We offer no cash alternative for non-cash prizes and prize winners must accept prizes in the form offered.
