Your use of the service or this Website after any revisions have been made constitutes Your acceptance of the new Terms and Conditions. If You do not agree to abide by these or any new Terms and Conditions, do not use or access (or continue to use or access) the service or this Website. It is Your responsibility to regularly check this page to determine if there have been changes to these Terms and Conditions and to consider such changes.
You should print a copy of these Terms and Conditions for future reference and You should also regularly revisit the Terms and Conditions on the Website for purposes of noting whether or not revisions have been made.
Who we are
1.1 Twinkl is the trading name of Twinkl Limited of Wards Exchange, 195-199 Ecclesall Road, Sheffield, S11 8HW, United Kingdom. Twinkl Limited is registered in England and Wales under company no. 07201458.
1.2. The term "Twinkl", "We" and "Us", shall mean Twinkl Limited, the owner of this Website. The term "You", "Yourself" and "Your" refers to the user or viewer of this Website.
1.3. Twinkl is the Data Controller within the definition of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
The services
2.1 Twinkl is a provider of high quality teaching resources - we call this the 'Service'. Our resources are primarily distributed through the Website.
2.2 Twinkl sells physical products and we call this the 'Product Service' which is made available through the Website.
2.3 Twinkl provides a range of resource membership services upon payment of a fee as specified on the Website or chargeable in some other way may be purchased. We call this the ‘Membership Service’.
2.4 Twinkl provides a support community forum service and we call this the ‘Forum Service’ which is made available through the Website.
2.5 We reserve the right to change pricing and or availability in respect of any of the services in this clause for any reason and without notice.
2.6 Twinkl is not responsible for non-delivery or technical limitations of the end user for any reason in respect of any of the services in this clause. You are strongly advised to read our
help and support FAQ
.
Member accounts
3.1 Certain aspects of the Services may require You to register and provide information about Yourself. You agree to: (a) provide true, accurate, current and complete information about Yourself as prompted by the relevant registration form contained on the Website (such information being the Registration Data) and (b) maintain and promptly update the Registration Data (by emailing Us) to keep it true, accurate, current and complete and We shall not be liable for any loss suffered by Your non-compliance with this provision.
3.2 Your privacy is incredibly important to us. You can find additional information in our
Privacy Policy
