Call Recordings Privacy Notice
Introduction
This notice is in addition to the
General Privacy Policy
. In the event that the Twinkl Call Recordings Privacy Notice conflicts with the General Privacy Policy, then the latter will prevail.
This privacy notice applies to telephone calls recorded by Twinkl Ltd. When a caller telephones Twinkl Ltd, the call is recorded. Such a call may contain personal data.
What is the purpose and legal grounds of call recordings?
The purpose of call recordings is to provide you with the best customer service possible. Best customer service possible means that we record your calls for:
training and quality services;
providing a record of your complaints or issues to investigate and rectify; and
ensuring our staff’s own security from abusive or mischievous calls
To use call recordings for the purposes described, we’ll rely on a condition known as legitimate interests, unless those interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the participants in the call.  You may therefore object to this processing if you think that your legitimate interests outweigh ours.
Who does Twinkl share call recordings with?
The call recordings may be shared with the following:
The Twinkl group of companies on a worldwide basis.
Third parties who deliver this service to you
Other third parties by law
How long does Twinkl retain call recordings?
We will retain calls for 18 months. However, this retention period may be extended if we need to rely on those recordings for legal proceedings.
What calls are recorded?
Calls which are recorded are: all inbound calls to Twinkl Customer and School Accounts team/helpdesks.
All callers are advised that calls will be recorded as part of a pre-recorded welcome message before being connected to Twinkl Ltd. The message states:
“Welcome to Twinkl Cares!  Just to let you know we record our calls to help us provide you with the best service possible. Don't want your call recorded? Email us at twinklcares@twinkl.com instead. Otherwise just stay on the line and we'll be with you soon.”
The message is followed by a beep/tone to indicate that the recording has started. The recording automatically stops when the caller disconnects from the call. You provide your agreement to the call recording by staying on the line after the pre-welcome message.
How can I contact Twinkl if I do not want to be recorded?
You may contact us by an alternative means such as mail or email.
Email:
 twinklcares@twinkl.co.uk or schools@twinkl.co.uk
Postal Address: Twinkl Global HQ, Wards Exchange, 197 Ecclesall Road, Sheffield, S11 8HW, UK
Where are call recordings stored?
Call recordings are stored by our Data Processor, on Zendesk Cloud Servers. We hold the appropriate legal documentation, as required by current data protection laws.
We may also download copies and store your call recordings on our encrypted servers for the purposes listed in this notice and for evidence in any legal proceedings.
Can I request a copy of a recording?
You may request a copy of a recorded telephone conversation, verbally or in writing. However, if we cannot verify your identity, we may request further identity information which may only be provided via further written communication. Only after obtaining all the relevant information to identify you, will we provide your recorded voice recordings within the current legal time frame of 1 month.
As with most subject access requests, there will be no fee for providing your information. However, we may charge a reasonable fee for the administrative costs of complying with a request if it is manifestly unfounded or excessive or if you require further copies of the data following a request.
When requesting a copy of a recorded telephone conversation please provide details to successfully identify you, the date and time of the call, if possible, in order to provide your information as quickly as possible to you (see the example below).
Call recording request form
Full name
Email address registered with your account
Username
Postal address
Month and Year  of  joining Twinkl
Date and time of call if possible
Date                               Approx Time
Format of data
WAV, MP3, CD-Rom, Transcript,
(Please delete unwanted options)
Data to be sent to….
Postal address/email
(Please delete unwanted options)
We have up to 30 days from the date of receipt of a valid and authenticated request but if you can provide the date range and the time of your call recording, we will be able to respond to your request more quickly.
A permanent copy of the recording will be provided in a format that Twinkl can reasonably expect the enquirer will be able to use; taking account of the enquirer’s preference (if any), practicality and cost of preparation. Formats could include WAV, MP3, other digital format or a transcript.
Please submit your request via email or to the postal address as above: twinklcares@twinkl.co.uk  or schools@twinkl.co.uk
Alternatively, use the contact information on our contact us page.
Will there be changes to this call recording policy?
Our Call Recording Policy may change from time to time due to changes in how we operate our business or in the UK legislation governing call recording. We will amend any changes to our Call Recording Policy on this page.
What are my rights?
Please refer to our General Privacy Policy.
What if I have concerns regarding Twinkl Ltd’s call recording policy?
If you have any concerns about this policy and your data protection rights, please contact the DPO at dpo@twinkl.co.uk
We will undertake to resolve directly with you any concerns that you may have. Should we not be able to,  then the matter can be addressed to the Information Commissioner’s Office at Wycliffe House, Water Lane, Wilmslow, Cheshire, SK9 5AF. Telephone number: 0303 123 1113.
