When you place your order to subscribe at the end of the online checkout process (e.g. when you click on the ‘Pay’ button), we will acknowledge your subscription to the Product Service by email. This is a
Subscription Confirmation Email
.
A Subscription Confirmation Email means that your order to subscribe to the Product Service has been accepted by us and you have subscribed to the Product Service. At this point, a legally binding contract will be in place between you and us.
We may send you a
Product Confirmation Email
within a reasonable time prior to our taking payment for and/or delivery of each Product.
If you are under the age of 18, you may not subscribe to any Product Service on our site.
You may not subscribe to any Product Service if you are not a consumer. If you are a business, please contact us at
https://www.twinkl.co.uk/contact-us
to register your interest for the Product Service.
Right to cancel
You have the right to cancel this subscription within 14 days without giving any reason.
You may cancel the subscription for the Product Service at any time provided that notice of such cancellation is received by us within the
Cancellation Period
in the relevant Product Service page.
You cannot cancel your subscription outside the Cancellation Period.
To exercise the right to cancel, you must inform us of your decision to cancel your subscription either via our website or by contacting us using a method set out here:
https://www.twinkl.co.uk/contact-us
. Your contract with us for the Product Service will be cancelled from the point at which we confirm your cancellation by notifying you of this.
We may cancel your subscription for the Product Service at any time prior to delivery of any Product. We will notify you by email if this occurs and refund you for any payment made for any Product which has not been delivered.
Effects of cancellation
If you cancel this contract and you have already made a payment for a Product which you have not yet received, we will refund to you all payments received.
We will make the reimbursement using the same means of payment as you used for the Product transaction, unless you have expressly agreed otherwise.
If you have cancelled this contract after a Product has been dispatched by us or delivered to you, we may make a deduction from the reimbursement for loss in value of any goods supplied and all delivery costs.
We may withhold reimbursement until we have received the Product back.
If you have received goods:
you shall send back the goods or hand them over to us without undue delay and in any event not later than 14 days from the day on which you communicate your cancellation from this contract to us. The deadline is met if you send the goods back before the period of 14 days has expired;
you will bear the cost of returning the goods; and
you are liable for any diminished value of the goods resulting from the handling other than what is necessary to establish the nature, characteristics and functioning of the goods.
Delivery
The estimated schedule for delivery of each Product in the Product Service is set out in the Product Service page from time to time or the Subscription Confirmation Email. If there is a conflict between the Product Service page and the Subscription Confirmation Email relating to the estimated delivery schedule of the Products in the Product Service, you must contact us. We may tell you which schedule is correct for the Product Service or inform you of an alternative delivery schedule.
The estimated delivery of each Product may be set out in any Product Confirmation Email sent to you before each Product delivery (‘the
Expected Arrival Date
’). If a Product Confirmation Email is not sent to you, the Expected Arrival Date of each Product is as described in the delivery schedule in clause 7.1.
If something happens which is outside of our control, the Expected Arrival Date may be affected. We may provide you with a revised Expected Arrival Date at any time.
You will not have a right to cancel or receive a refund for non-delivery unless the product has not been delivered within a reasonable time following the month of the Expected Arrival Date.
If a Product has not been delivered by the Expected Arrival Date, you must contact us at
https://www.twinkl.co.uk/contact-us
. We may either arrange for a replacement Product to be delivered to you or a refund for that Product at our discretion.
Delivery will take place as the address specified by you when you placed your order with us for the Product Service. If you wish to change this address for any delivery of the ongoing Product Service, please contact us at
https://www.twinkl.co.uk/contact-us
.
Each Product is separate and non-delivery of one Product does not affect the contract for the remaining Products prior to cancellation of this contract.
Payment
We will do all that we reasonably can to ensure that all of the information you give us when submitting your payment details for the Product Service is secure by using an encrypted secure payment mechanism. However, in the absence of negligence on our part, any failure by us to comply with this contract or our Privacy Policy (see clause 3) or breach by us of our duties under applicable laws, we will not be legally responsible to you for any loss that you may suffer if a third party gains unauthorised access to any information that you give us.
Your payment method will be charged prior to dispatch of each Product.
If your payment is not received by us and you have already received a Product, you must:
pay for such Product as soon as possible and in any case within 30 days of receipt of the Product; or
return the Product to us as soon as possible and in any case within 30 days of receipt of the Product. If so, you must keep the Product in your possession until you return it to us, take reasonable care of it whilst it is in your possession, and not use the Product prior to returning it to us.
If you do not pay for the Product or fail to return the Product in accordance with clause 8.3, we may collect the Product from you at your expense. We will try to contact you to let you know if we intend to do this.
Nothing in this clause affects your legal rights to cancel the contract during the Cancellation Period.
Nature of the Product
The Consumer Rights Act 2015 gives you certain legal rights (also known as ‘statutory rights’). The Product(s) that we provide to you must be as described, fit for purpose and of satisfactory quality.
We are under a legal duty to supply you with Products that are in conformity with this contract.
The packaging of the Product(s) may be different from that shown on the site.
While we try to make sure that:
all weights, sizes and measurements set out on the Product Service page are as accurate as possible, there may be a small tolerance of up to 5% in such weights, sizes and measurements; and
the colours of the Product are displayed accurately on the site, the actual colours that you see on your device may vary depending on the device that you use.
End of the contract
If this contract is ended it will not affect our right to receive any money which you owe to us under this contract.
Limitation on our liability
Except for any legal responsibility that we cannot exclude in law (such as for death or personal injury) or arising under applicable laws relating to the protection of your personal information, we are not legally responsible for any:
losses that were not foreseeable to you and us when the contract was formed;
losses that were not caused by any breach on our part;
business losses; or
losses to non-consumers.
Third party rights
No one other than a party to this contract has any right to enforce any term of this contract.
Disputes
We will try to resolve any disputes with you quickly and efficiently. If you are unhappy with a Product, the Product Service, or any other matter, please contact us as soon as possible using the contact details at
https://www.twinkl.co.uk/contact-us
The laws of England and Wales apply to this contract. Any disputes will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
